# Aegis Linux - Local AppArmor Profile Overrides
# =============================================================================
#
# This directory contains local customizations to AppArmor profiles.
# Files here will NOT be overwritten during system updates.
#
# To add custom rules to a profile:
#
# 1. Create a file matching the profile name
#    Example: For Firefox profile "usr.bin.firefox", create:
#    /etc/apparmor.d/local/usr.bin.firefox
#
# 2. Add your custom rules to this file
#    Example content:
#    # Allow access to custom directory
#    /home/*/.custom-app/** rw,
#
# 3. Reload the profile:
#    sudo apparmor_parser -r /etc/apparmor.d/usr.bin.firefox
#
# Common rule syntax:
#   r  - read
#   w  - write
#   x  - execute
#   l  - link
#   k  - lock
#   m  - memory map executable
#
# Wildcards:
#   *  - matches any characters except /
#   ** - matches any characters including /
#   ?  - matches single character
#
# For more information:
#   https://gitlab.com/apparmor/apparmor/-/wikis/QuickProfileLanguage
#
# To transition profiles from complain to enforce mode:
#   sudo aa-enforce /etc/apparmor.d/usr.bin.firefox
#
# To check current profile status:
#   sudo aa-status
#
